{"lemma":"لِصٌّ","slug":"لِصٌّ","root":"ل.ص.ص","root_slug":"ل-ص-ص","root_link":"/words/roots/ل-ص-ص","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":12},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n37730"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%84%D9%90%D8%B5%D9%8C%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"thief, robber","examples":[{"text":"مَكَانَكَ أَيُّهَا ٱللِّصُّ!","english":"Stop there, thief!"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"thief","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to steal","tags":["obsolete","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to do secretly","tags":["obsolete","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to close (the door)","tags":["obsolete","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be a thief, to be thievish, to steal repeatedly"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have teeth close together"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have hunched shoulders, to stoop (of a person or horse)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have one's thighs close together (of a woman)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be narrow (of one's forehead)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have unevenly oriented horns (of a sheep)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of لَصَّ (laṣṣa, “to steal, to do secretly, to close (the door)”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","obsolete","transitive"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Ancient Greek λῃστής (lēistḗs)."},"ipa":["/lisˤsˤ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n37730","headword_ar":"لِصٌّ","root":"lS","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luS~N","text_ar":"لُصٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) the latter mentioned by As, (Msb,) but only the former known to Sb, (M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laS~N","text_ar":"لَصٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IDrd, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thief; a robber;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, Msb, K;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laSotN","text_ar":"لَصْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"substituted for the [second]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"S","text_ar":"ص"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the form of the word changed because of the substitution, or it is a dial. form of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liS~N","text_ar":"لِصٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and is said by Lh to be of the dial. of Teiyi and of some of the Ansár, and also pronounced"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liSotN","text_ar":"لِصْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luSotN","text_ar":"لُصْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lSt","text_ar":"لصت"},{"kind":"text","text":":) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liS~apN","text_ar":"لِصَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laS~apN","text_ar":"لَصَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, K:) pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liS~N","text_ar":"لِصٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luS~N","text_ar":"لُصٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laS~N","text_ar":"لَصٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IDrd, K,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luSuwSN","text_ar":"لُصُوصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IDrd, S, M, Msb, K,) and of the first,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liSaSapN","text_ar":"لِصَصَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IDrd, TA,) and of the first (M, TA) and second, (M,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liSaASN","text_ar":"لِصَاصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aloSaASN","text_ar":"اَلْصَاصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2660},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) [and in the TA said to be so in the T: but this is probably a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liSaASN","text_ar":"لِصَاصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": for ISd says,] the word has no pl. of pauc.: (M:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malaS~apN","text_ar":"مَلَصَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a quasi-pl. n.: (IJ, M:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liS~apN","text_ar":"لِصَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laS~apN","text_ar":"لَصَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liS~aAtN","text_ar":"لِصَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laS~aAtN","text_ar":"لَصَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laSaAy^iSu","text_ar":"لَصَايِصُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) which last is extr. [with respect to rule]: (M:) and the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liSotN","text_ar":"لِصْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luSuwtN","text_ar":"لُصُوتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","A","Msb","K","IDrd","TA","IJ"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}